        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 2:50PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 250 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Warm Springs, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...

Locations impacted include...
Goshen...
Millboro...
Warm Springs...
Nimrod Hall...
Burnsville...
Yost...
and Mountain Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
